org.usfirst.frc.team302.robot.subsystems

Class Drive

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Subsystem
      • org.usfirst.frc.team302.robot.subsystems.Drive
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.NamedSendable, edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.Sendable

    public class Drive
extends edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Subsystem
    This subsystem defines the drive subsystem for the robot. It controls the talons/motors for the drive as well as processes the encoder values.
    Version:
    version 1: 1/16/2016 -- Derek Witcpalek -- original dummy class, version 2: 2/1/2016 -- Eric Smith and Klayton Smith -- Fill in the details, version 3: 2/21/2016 -- Derek Witcpalek -- Update with turn control for arcade drive, version 4: 2/21/2016 -- Klayton Smith -- Cross obstacle, version 5: 2/27/2016 -- Josh Baker -- lowBar + implemented navX wrapper, version 6: 3/3/2016 -- Derek Witcpalek -- Add Jeff's turn to angle and vision-based orientation, version 7: 3/3/2016 -- Joe Witcpalek Merge -- Derek's changes with the latest version, version 8: 3/3/2016 -- Joe Witcpalek Add Review comments

        Parameters:

        rotateValue - value for rotating the robot

      • tankDrive

        public void tankDrive(double leftValue,
                      double rightValue)
        Drive the robot by providing the forward/backward value for each side of the robot. Turning is achieved by providing different values to each side.
        Parameters:
        leftValue - speed of the left side of the robot
        rightValue - speed of the right side of the robot
